			<h1 class="post-title">Avoiding fast-forward merges in Git</h1>

			<p>Just a pointer to an excellent post I wanted to share with you:</p>
<p>In the section &#8220;Why we shouldnâ€™t fast-forward&#8221; at <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/robey.lag.net/2009/11/29/more-git.html');"  href="http://robey.lag.net/2009/11/29/more-git.html">http://robey.lag.net/2009/11/29/more-git.html</a>, Robey explains very clearly how fast forwards effectively make you loose historical information that may be crucial to ever reconstruct or understand your own project&#8217;s history.</p>

						
